        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 9:19PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 919 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles south of Parker School, or 22 miles east of Big Sandy, moving
northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lloyd.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
